<br>
grey - 3 or more levels lower<br>
green - 2 lower<br>
blue - 1 lower<br>
yellow - even<br>
orange - 1 above<br>
red - 2 above<br>
purple - 3 or more above<br>
<br>
I've had a couple occurances that didn't fit this, but overall this seems accurate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=pril>Pril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/21/01 12:17:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yellow con??</span><hr size=1> well Zad said he had a yellow Con staff, someone else referred to a orange con staff. How does this fit in?<br>
